{
  "texts": [
    "The main difference between the source building and the target buildings lies in the integration of PV system and BESS on the energy system.",
    "A 3-kW nominal power for the PV system is selected to align with the peak power requirement of the overall electrical demand of the building.",
    "The PV system is modelled in the simulation environment by means of a Python class as in Brandi et al. 2022(b), and employing solar position data from the Python library pvlib (Holmgren et al. 2018).",
    "The PV system consists of monocrystalline silicon modules, each having a nominal power of 200 W/m 2 and efficiency (η) defined in Equation (1) and equal to 15%.",
    "The efficiency of PV modules is evaluated under standard conditions (i.e., solar irradiance G STC = 1000 W/m 2, cell temperature T STC = 25 °C, air mass AM STC = 1.5) as described in Durisch et al. (2007)."
  ]
}